## **Adept**
**_Prerequisite: 5th level_**

_Each ability costs 2 talent points_

**Abilities:**
- **Earthen Resilience:** Gain proficiency in Constitution saving throws.
- **Terramancer:** Gain expertise (double proficiency bonus) in Athletics when performing tasks involving lifting, pushing, or pulling heavy objects made of stone or earth.
- **Stone Camouflage:** You have advantage on Stealth checks to hide in rocky terrain or against stone surfaces.
- **Earthen Grasp:** You can use an action to cause the ground to grasp a creature within 30 feet, restraining it for 1 minute. The target can make a Strength saving throw at the end of each of its turns to break free. You can use this feature after a long rest.
- **Stone Armor:** As a bonus action, you can encase yourself in a layer of stone, granting you resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage for 1 minute. You can use this feature after a short or long rest.
- **Sandstorm:** As an action, you create a swirling storm of sand in a 20-foot radius centred on you. Each creature in the area must make a Constitution saving throw, taking 3d6 bludgeoning damage on a failed save and becoming blinded until the end of their next turn, or half as much damage on a successful save. The storm lasts for 1 minute. The area is difficult terrain, any creature that starts its turn within the storm takes 1d6 damage. This ability can be used once per long rest. This ability’s range increases by 10-foot when you reach 9th Master level (30-foot radius), 13th Grandmaster level (40-foot radius) and 17th Great-grandmaster level (50-foot radius).

**3rd Level Spells:**
